  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a moderate amount of money and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a breach of fiduciary trust, the lack of prior criminal history and the commitment to repayment warrant a period of incarceration that emphasizes rehabilitation over long-term punitive detention. A six-month term is sufficient to punish the crime and deter future misconduct without causing undue hardship to a first-time non-violent offender.",
  "verdict": 6
}
